table.name: auto_mod_anti_dup
table.Comment: Represents the Anti Duplicates configuration\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: auto_mod_auto_raid
table.Comment:
Represents The AutoRaid configuration. This
is used to determine if autoraid is enabled
and the threshhold to look back in time to see
how many users have joined the server recently
@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: auto_mod_ignore
table.Comment: Represents the the roles and in what channel\nwill be ignored (text) when AutoModeration is enabled\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: auto_mod_mentions
table.Comment:
Represents the max number of role mentions(@everyone),
max number of lines allowed in a text message, and the max number
of mentions a discord user may write.
@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: auto_moderation
table.Comment: Represents the automoderation configuration\nfor a specific guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: discord_user
table.Comment: Represents a physical Discord user used by Guildo.\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: discord_user_profile
table.Comment: Represents the Guildo Bot profile for a specific\nDiscord User.\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: give_away
table.Comment: Represents A Giveaway which a Guild User may create\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_application
table.Comment: Represents an application to a specific guild from a discord user\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_application_form
table.Comment: Represents the Application Form (doc,txt, etc.) which a Discord User\nmay need to fillout and submit within their application\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_event
table.Comment: Represents an Event owned by a guild (raid, dungeon, etc)\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_poll
table.Comment: Represents a Poll an authorized Discord User\nmay create in a particular Guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_poll_item
table.Comment: Represents an Item which will be placed\ninto the Poll. Used to create a list of items.\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_server
table.Comment: Represents a Guild Server (Discord Server)\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_server_profile
table.Comment: Represents the specific details of a Guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: guild_server_settings
table.Comment: Represents the Guildo settings of a particular Guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: moderation_log_item
table.Comment: Represents a Log Entry of all Moderator\nspecific actions on Users (kicks, bans, etc.)\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: mute
table.Comment: Represents a temprary muting of a Discord user within a guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: punishment
table.Comment: Represents the a punishment a moderator\nmay hand to a Discord User in their server\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: scheduled_announcement
table.Comment: Represents an Annoucement which will be broadcasted\nacross a Discord Server at a later date\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: server_log_item
table.Comment: Represents a Log entry of all service specific events (name changes, avatar change, etc)\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: temp_ban
table.Comment: Represents a temporary ban of a Discord user from a guild\n@author Mark Tripoli

table.name: welcome_message
table.Comment: Represents A welcome message used to greet\nnew users to a Guild\n@author Mark Tripoli
